description.narrative: To contribute to the strategic sanitation objectives, UNICEF has set up an innovative project to create and promote improved toilets with lids. Launched in 2019 to benefit the most disadvantaged households in rural areas, this project is very successful because in 2021, 2305 new users were registered. Also, more than 1,830 new users from non-beneficiary villages have equipped themselves using their own means. This is a positive sign regarding the sustainability of the project achievements. For the water sector, an inventory of water resources was created and monitoring was made systematic thanks to the SIEC project. | Status:Met | As-of Date:11/01/2022
